08/06/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Visiting Tirana on Tuesday (7 June), Council of Europe Secretary General Terry Davis reiterated the importance of the 3 July parliamentary elections and praised efforts by President Alfred Moisiu to ensure a free and democratic vote.
Moisiu has met with representatives of the media, the state police, the army and other institutions in preparation for the elections.
Also Tuesday, opposition leader Sali Berisha of the Democratic Party agreed to a televised debate with Prime Minister Fatos Nano of the ruling Socialist Party.
The date has not been determined.
(Albanian News - 08/06/05;
Albanian President Web site, CoE Web site - 07/06/05)
